OH THOU ! who poured the patriotic tide , That streamed through great , unhappy WALLACE' heart ; Who dared to , nobly , stem tyrannic pride , Or nobly die , the second glorious part : ( The Patriot's GOD , peculiarly thou art , His friend , inspirer , guardian and reward ! )
